{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-sermons-list-js","path":"/en/sermons/page/637","result":{"pageContext":{"pagination":{"total":1038,"current":637},"lang":"en","nodes":[{"id":"21158","title":"How to be Human Again","imageWithFallback":{"url":"https://s.audioverse.org/english/gallery/persons/_/50/50/Ritsma-Scott2020.jpg"},"persons":[{"name":"Scott Ritsema"}],"duration":3819.4,"recordingDate":"2020-01-02T09:30:00.000Z","audioFiles":[{"url":"https://www.audioverse.org/english/download/dl/73271/2020/01/21158/20200102-0930-21158-f4ba434b994c20e322c5c99678ce918f-64k.mp3"},{"url":"https://www.audioverse.org/english/download/dl/73348/2020/01/21158/20200102-0930-21158-f4ba434b994c20e322c5c99678ce918f-48k.mp3"},{"url":"https://www.audioverse.org/english/download/dl/73349/2020/01/21158/20200102-0930-21158-f4ba434b994c20e322c5c99678ce918f-16k.mp3"}],"description":"<p>It goes without saying - media use is out of control and may be the single biggest stumbling block in spiritual, social and family life today. Which begs the question: what does the latest research say about the stranglehold of 'big tech' upon our lives and how to break free? What are the essential biblical principles for establishing a balanced use of technological tools? And how can we truly restore spirituality and relationships in the digital age?</p>"},{"id":"21247","title":"Looking for Interested Hearers","imageWithFallback":{"url":"https://s.audioverse.org/english/gallery/persons/_/50/50/Wright_David.jpg"},"persons":[{"name":"David Wright"}],"duration":2567.8,"recordingDate":"2019-04-06T12:30:00.000Z","audioFiles":[{"url":"https://www.audioverse.org/english/download/dl/73033/2020/01/21247/20200406-1230-21247-0a17f245c1650a18af9d2b8a8408c361-96k.mp3"},{"url":"https://www.audioverse.org/english/download/dl/73035/2020/01/21247/20200406-1230-21247-0a17f245c1650a18af9d2b8a8408c361-48k.mp3"},{"url":"https://www.audioverse.org/english/download/dl/73036/2020/01/21247/20200406-1230-21247-0a17f245c1650a18af9d2b8a8408c361-16k.mp3"}],"description":""},{"id":"21028","title":"06-Dying for Devotions","imageWithFallback":{"url":"https://s.audioverse.org/english/gallery/seriess/1/50/50/InverseLogo.jpg"},"persons":[{"name":"Sebastien Braxton"},{"name":"Sikhu Daco"},{"name":"Callie Williams"}],"duration":2033.4,"recordingDate":"2020-02-08T09:45:00.000Z","audioFiles":[{"url":"https://www.audioverse.org/english/download/dl/72559/2019/12/21028/20200208-0945-21028-916ea15e12d9f540f1d8d72fb56e379d-96k.mp3"},{"url":"https://www.audioverse.org/english/download/dl/72560/2019/12/21028/20200208-0945-21028-916ea15e12d9f540f1d8d72fb56e379d-48k.mp3"},{"url":"https://www.audioverse.org/english/download/dl/72561/2019/12/21028/20200208-0945-21028-916ea15e12d9f540f1d8d72fb56e379d-16k.mp3"}],"description":"<p>The dynamics of an effective devotional life.</p>"},{"id":"21190","title":"Final Charge: Make Adventism Good Again","imageWithFallback":{"url":"https://s.audioverse.org/english/gallery/persons/_/50/50/Ramos_Israel.jpg"},"persons":[{"name":"Israel Ramos"}],"duration":7981.4,"recordingDate":"2020-01-04T17:30:00.000Z","audioFiles":[{"url":"https://www.audioverse.org/english/download/dl/73276/2020/01/21190/20200104-1730-21190-47150ae08e899bd2d15b97fb3a40f171-64k.mp3"},{"url":"https://www.audioverse.org/english/download/dl/73302/2020/01/21190/20200104-1730-21190-47150ae08e899bd2d15b97fb3a40f171-48k.mp3"},{"url":"https://www.audioverse.org/english/download/dl/73303/2020/01/21190/20200104-1730-21190-47150ae08e899bd2d15b97fb3a40f171-16k.mp3"}],"description":""},{"id":"21188","title":"What About the Few","imageWithFallback":{"url":"https://s.audioverse.org/english/gallery/conferences/1/50/50/GYC-2019-ByManyorByFew.jpg"},"persons":[{"name":"Samuel  Thomas"}],"duration":6313,"recordingDate":"2020-01-04T11:00:00.000Z","audioFiles":[{"url":"https://www.audioverse.org/english/download/dl/73172/2020/01/21188/20200104-1100-21188-d057f032618d6305a811d183d9aa8158-64k.mp3"},{"url":"https://www.audioverse.org/english/download/dl/73220/2020/01/21188/20200104-1100-21188-d057f032618d6305a811d183d9aa8158-48k.mp3"},{"url":"https://www.audioverse.org/english/download/dl/73221/2020/01/21188/20200104-1100-21188-d057f032618d6305a811d183d9aa8158-16k.mp3"}],"description":"<p>Jesus told us in Matthew 24, the world will increase in conflict, become more unpredictable in natural disasters, and intensify in deception. September 12th, 2019 Pope Francis announced an initiative inviting global heads of state, business leaders, academic leaders, and sport personalities to Rome May 14, 2020. His theme: Reinventing the Global Educational Alliance. His purpose: Reeducating the world to a new perspective in environmental stewardship. His goal: The unification of people and religions.</p>"},{"id":"21187","title":"Sabbath School","imageWithFallback":{"url":"https://s.audioverse.org/english/gallery/conferences/1/50/50/GYC-2019-ByManyorByFew.jpg"},"persons":[{"name":"Sebastien Braxton"},{"name":"Sikhu Daco"},{"name":"Justin Kim"},{"name":"Israel Ramos"},{"name":"Jonathan Walter"}],"duration":4400,"recordingDate":"2020-01-04T09:30:00.000Z","audioFiles":[{"url":"https://www.audioverse.org/english/download/dl/73173/2020/01/21187/20200104-0930-21187-025b5f6167a1a9a7e3f83cd370b15430-64k.mp3"},{"url":"https://www.audioverse.org/english/download/dl/73222/2020/01/21187/20200104-0930-21187-025b5f6167a1a9a7e3f83cd370b15430-48k.mp3"},{"url":"https://www.audioverse.org/english/download/dl/73223/2020/01/21187/20200104-0930-21187-025b5f6167a1a9a7e3f83cd370b15430-16k.mp3"}],"description":""},{"id":"21183","title":"Kingmakers","imageWithFallback":{"url":"https://s.audioverse.org/english/gallery/persons/_/50/50/Cullinane_Dean.jpg"},"persons":[{"name":"Dean Cullinane"}],"duration":5281.8,"recordingDate":"2020-01-03T18:30:00.000Z","audioFiles":[{"url":"https://www.audioverse.org/english/download/dl/73177/2020/01/21183/20200103-1830-21183-d6ef282e726ffede1b1ae0d899bc92fe-64k.mp3"},{"url":"https://www.audioverse.org/english/download/dl/73232/2020/01/21183/20200103-1830-21183-d6ef282e726ffede1b1ae0d899bc92fe-48k.mp3"},{"url":"https://www.audioverse.org/english/download/dl/73233/2020/01/21183/20200103-1830-21183-d6ef282e726ffede1b1ae0d899bc92fe-16k.mp3"}],"description":"<p>The final plenary will be something of a character study on the life of Jonathan and specifically his relationship with David, as expressed in 1 Sam 18. What can we learn from these ancient friends, and how might this relationship change the future of adventism?</p>"},{"id":"21182","title":"The Great Gates of Hell","imageWithFallback":{"url":"https://s.audioverse.org/english/gallery/persons/_/50/50/Cullinane_Dean.jpg"},"persons":[{"name":"Dean Cullinane"}],"duration":5441.6,"recordingDate":"2020-01-02T18:30:00.000Z","audioFiles":[{"url":"https://www.audioverse.org/english/download/dl/73178/2020/01/21182/20200102-1830-21182-34d42095d6e6b0d3349c5383942f50b0-64k.mp3"},{"url":"https://www.audioverse.org/english/download/dl/73234/2020/01/21182/20200102-1830-21182-34d42095d6e6b0d3349c5383942f50b0-48k.mp3"},{"url":"https://www.audioverse.org/english/download/dl/73235/2020/01/21182/20200102-1830-21182-34d42095d6e6b0d3349c5383942f50b0-16k.mp3"}],"description":"<p>The second plenary will be looking at the importance of True Education as it relates to the Three Angels Message.</p>\r\n<p>What is the purpose of our academic institutions today, and how can we make a difference as mere students?</p>"},{"id":"21136","title":"A Thousand Shall Run","imageWithFallback":{"url":"https://s.audioverse.org/english/gallery/persons/_/50/50/Cullinane_Dean.jpg"},"persons":[{"name":"Dean Cullinane"}],"duration":6274.8,"recordingDate":"2020-01-01T18:00:00.000Z","audioFiles":[{"url":"https://www.audioverse.org/english/download/dl/73420/2020/01/21136/20200101-1800-21136-8060b7b0508e04cdb832225bf2c426a1-64k.mp3"}],"description":"<p>1 Sam 14:6 tells of Jonathan's brave foray against the camp of the Philistines. Was this really faith? Or was it presumption? How can we be sure of the difference between the two, and what significance might this have for God's last day church?</p>"},{"id":"21153","title":"How to Interpret Scripture: How do we Approach the Bible with Serious Questions? Facing the Major (and Minor) Issues","imageWithFallback":{"url":"https://s.audioverse.org/english/gallery/persons/_/50/50/hasel_michael.jpg"},"persons":[{"name":"Michael Hasel"}],"duration":4739,"recordingDate":"2020-01-02T14:30:00.000Z","audioFiles":[{"url":"https://www.audioverse.org/english/download/dl/73207/2020/01/21153/20200102-1430-21153-2e21e123b1dbd1a0ebf438cedeeacd2a-64k.mp3"},{"url":"https://www.audioverse.org/english/download/dl/73242/2020/01/21153/20200102-1430-21153-2e21e123b1dbd1a0ebf438cedeeacd2a-48k.mp3"},{"url":"https://www.audioverse.org/english/download/dl/73245/2020/01/21153/20200102-1430-21153-2e21e123b1dbd1a0ebf438cedeeacd2a-16k.mp3"}],"description":"<p>How do we face the crucial questions that confront us in society and culture? How do we interpret the Bible in the face of significant challenges in science, history and prophecy? What about the bigger issues facing our church? This seminar seeks to answer these crucial questions by pointing us back to basic principles of biblical interpretation that will guide our understanding of the living Word of God with the assurance that it is more relevant today than it has ever been.</p>"}]}},"staticQueryHashes":["3649515864"]}